{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, a static data source, a digital elevation map (DEM), was used to derive and precompute specific features.",
    "9, a DBN model with two RBM layers exhibits this structure.",
    "In an RBM, the visible layer (v) is utilized to input training data, while the hidden layer (h) extracts data features, with both layers being bidirectionally linked.",
    "The first RBM's hidden layer functions as the second RBM's visible layer.",
    "635The SSMIS-observed brightness temperature data has been gridded to the EASE-Grid, providing a daily temporal resolution and a spatial resolution of 25 km."
  ]
}